## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="2b11e-104">Per impostazione predefinita, il nome del metodo WMI sarà il nome del metodo di destinazione.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="2b11e-104">By default, the WMI method name will be the name of the target method.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="2b11e-105">La classe padre di questo attributo, <xref:System.Management.Instrumentation.ManagementMemberAttribute>, include un parametro Name.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="2b11e-105">The parent class of this attribute, <xref:System.Management.Instrumentation.ManagementMemberAttribute>, includes a Name parameter.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="2b11e-106">È possibile utilizzare il parametro per modificare il nome del metodo che viene esposta tramite WMI senza modificare il nome del metodo interno.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="2b11e-106">You can use that parameter to change the name of the method that is exposed through WMI without changing your internal method name.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="2b11e-107">Il metodo deve essere pubblico e può essere statico.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="2b11e-107">The method must be public and it may be static.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="2b11e-108">Può includere qualsiasi combinazione di [in], [out], [in/out] matrice o un oggetto parametri per riferimento.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="2b11e-108">It can include any combination of [in], [out], [in/out], array or object reference parameters.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="2b11e-109">I parametri di matrice non possono essere multidimensionali o di matrice a causa delle limitazioni imposte da WMI.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="2b11e-109">Array parameters cannot be multidimensional or jagged because of limitations imposed by WMI.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="2b11e-110">Il tipo restituito del metodo può essere: void, scalare, string, datetime o dell'oggetto.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="2b11e-110">The return type of the method can be: void, scalar, string, datetime or object.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="2b11e-111">Non può essere una matrice.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="2b11e-111">It cannot be an array.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="2b11e-112">Nell'esempio seguente viene illustrato come contrassegnare un metodo con l'attributo ManagementTask per esporre il metodo a WMI.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="2b11e-112">The following example shows how to mark a method with the ManagementTask attribute to expose the method to WMI.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="2b11e-113">Il metodo appariranno in WMI come ResetCounters.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="2b11e-113">The method will show up in WMI as ResetCounters.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
// Use the ManagementTask attribute to specify that a method  
// is exposed to WMI through this provider. Consumers will be  
// able to execute this method through WMI.  
[ManagementTask]  
public void ResetCounters()  
{  
    counter.Reset();  
}  
```
